column2: Overview Come and join us!  Do you want to advance your career with the worlds first cloud company? Since 1998, Oracle NetSuite has been on a mission to deliver an agile, unified application suite that gives leaders a complete view into their business. Our team is growing, and were looking for people like you to help us make a global impact. As the leading cloud business system, NetSuite includes financials, inventory management, HR, professional services automation, commerce, and more. Tens of thousands of customers all over the world trust NetSuite to give their businesses the visibility, agility, and control needed to make data-informed decisions quickly.  NetSuite is a place where you can build your career and have fun while doing so! Were invested in our people, our customers, and the community. As part of Oracle, our benefits are second to none. Joining our passionate team means that you??e ready to take your career to the next level. Key responsibilities include providing ad hoc support to various departments, developing and publishing Power BI reports, evaluating and implementing new procedures and technologies, collaborating with cross-functional teams to gather business and reporting requirements, analysing disparate database sources, serving as a subject matter expert for reporting and dashboards, and extracting data to create data models using various tools and connectors. Essential Experience 3 to 5 years of experience in Power BI and SQL Server query writing.

column2: Verve Global Solution is a leading financial services company committed to delivering innovative solutions and insights to our clients in the ever-evolving financial landscape. We are dedicated to leveraging data analytics to drive informed decision-making and empower our clients to achieve their financial goals. As part of our commitment to excellence, we are seeking a talented Power BI Developer with expertise in the financial domain to join our dynamic team. Role Overview: We are looking for an experienced Power BI Developer with a strong background in the financial domain to design, develop, and implement BI solutions that provide actionable insights into financial data. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of financial concepts and metrics, along with proven experience in building advanced Power BI reports and dashboards tailored for financial analysis and reporting. Responsibilities: 1. Design, develop, and maintain complex Power BI reports and dashboards utilizing advanced features such as bookmarks, drill-through, and custom visuals. 2. Implement advanced data modeling techniques using Power BI Desktop, including creating calculated columns, measures, and hierarchies using DAX (Data Analysis Expressions). 3. Utilize Power Query for data transformation tasks such as merging, appending, and unpivoting data from multiple sources including MySQL databases, SQL Server, Excel files, and REST APIs. 4. Develop and optimize data models using techniques such as star schema design, role-playing dimensions, and bidirectional filtering to ensure efficient performance and scalability. 5. Implement row-level security (RLS) and dynamic security models to restrict access to sensitive data based on user roles and permissions. 6. Collaborate with database administrators and data engineers to optimize MySQL database performance and ensure seamless integration with Power BI. 7. Provide technical guidance and mentorship to junior members of the team on Power BI best practices, data modeling, and performance optimization. 8. Stay current with the latest Power BI features and updates, evaluating their potential impact on existing solutions and recommending adoption where applicable. 9. Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to Power BI reports, data refresh failures, and performance bottlenecks in collaboration with IT support teams. Requirements: 1. Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Computer Science, or related field. 2. Minimum of  3  years of experience as a Power BI Developer or similar role in the financial services industry. 3. Deep understanding of financial concepts, metrics, and reporting requirements. 4. Proficiency in Microsoft Power BI, including advanced data modeling techniques, DAX calculations, and Power Query transformations. 5. Experience working with financial databases such as SQL Server, Oracle, or MySQL. 6. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate complex financial requirements into effective Power BI solutions. 7. Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to interact effectively with finance professionals and business stakeholders. 8. Relevant certifications such as Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate or similar credentials preferred. Additional Note: Candidate may have to relocate to UAE or other Southeast Asian nation, and this position will be remote.

column2: We are seeking an experienced Power BI Developer to join our data visualization and analytics team. As a Power BI Developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining interactive and insightful data visualizations, reports, and dashboards that provide valuable insights to our stakeholders. Your expertise in data visualization and your proficiency in Power BI will play a pivotal role in transforming complex data into actionable business intelligence.       Key Responsibilities:           Data Visualization:    Collaborate with business analysts and data engineers to understand data requirements and translate them into effective visualizations and reports using Power BI.       Dashboard Development:    Design and build interactive and user-friendly dashboards that display key performance indicators (KPIs), trends, and insights, enabling data-driven decision-making.       Data Modeling:    Create and optimize data models within Power BI, ensuring efficient data storage, relationships, and calculations to support accurate and responsive visualizations.       Report Development:    Develop and maintain a variety of reports, including standard and ad-hoc reports, drill-through reports, and paginated reports, catering to different business needs.       Data Integration:    Integrate data from multiple sources into Power BI, including relational databases, data warehouses, APIs, and flat files, ensuring data accuracy and consistency.       Performance Optimization:    Optimize Power BI reports and dashboards for improved performance, responsiveness, and user experience.       Data Exploration:    Explore and analyze data to identify trends, patterns, and insights, and communicate findings effectively through compelling visualizations.       User Training:    Provide training and support to end users on how to use Power BI to access and interact with data visualizations, empowering them to extract valuable insights.       Documentation:    Create and maintain technical documentation, including data definitions, report specifications, and design guidelines, to facilitate knowledge sharing and maintain consistency.       Collaboration:    Work closely with data stakeholders, analysts, and business users to gather requirements, validate visualizations, and refine reports based on feedback.         Qualifications:         Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business Analytics, or related field (or equivalent work experience).       Minimum 5 years of professional experience    in data visualization and Power BI development.     Proficiency in Power BI Desktop, Power Query, DAX (Data Analysis Expressions), and Power BI Service.     Strong understanding of data visualization best practices, dashboard design, and user experience principles.     Experience with data preparation, transformation, and integration using Power Query.     Knowledge of data modeling concepts and familiarity with database systems.     Solid analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to translate business requirements into actionable insights.     Effective communication skills and the ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams.     Familiarity with data governance, data quality, and data security considerations.     Experience with other data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, QlikView) is a plus.     Knowledge of SQL and scripting languages (e.g., Python) is an advantage.     Experience with cloud-based data solutions (e.g., AWS, Azure, Google Cloud) is a plus.

column2: Role & responsibilities     Data Modeling : Designing and implementing data models that are optimized for reporting and analytics in Power BI. This involves understanding the underlying data sources, relationships between different data sets, and creating efficient data models using Power BI Desktop. Data Transformation : Extracting, transforming, and loading (ETL) data from various sources into Power BI. This may involve using Power Query to clean, transform, and reshape data before loading it into the data model. Dashboard and Report Development : Creating interactive dashboards and reports in Power BI Desktop or the Power BI Service. This includes selecting appropriate visualizations, designing layouts, and implementing interactivity to provide actionable insights to end-users. Data Visualization : Choosing the right visualizations (e.g., charts, graphs, maps) to effectively communicate data insights. This involves understanding data visualization best practices and tailoring visualizations to the needs of the audience. Performance Optimization : Optimizing the performance of Power BI reports and dashboards to ensure fast loading times and smooth interactivity. This may involve techniques such as data model optimization, query optimization, and leveraging Power BI's performance features. Data Governance and Security : Implementing data governance policies and security measures to ensure data privacy, integrity, and compliance with regulations. This includes managing access controls, role-based security, and data encryption within Power BI. Collaboration and Integration : Collaborating with stakeholders, data analysts, and other team members to gather requirements, iterate on designs, and deliver solutions that meet business needs. This may also involve integrating Power BI with other Microsoft products (e.g., Azure, SQL Server, Excel) or third-party tools.

Effective communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams. Self-motivated and able to work independently with minimal supervision. Power BI certification and SAP HANA certification are desirable.

column2: Verve Global Solution is a leading financial services company committed to delivering innovative solutions and insights to our clients in the ever-evolving financial landscape. We are dedicated to leveraging data analytics to drive informed decision-making and empower our clients to achieve their financial goals. As part of our commitment to excellence, we are seeking a talented Power BI Developer with expertise in the financial domain to join our dynamic team. Role Overview: We are looking for an experienced Power BI Developer with a strong background in the financial domain to design, develop, and implement BI solutions that provide actionable insights into financial data. The ideal candidate will have a deep understanding of financial concepts and metrics, along with proven experience in building advanced Power BI reports and dashboards tailored for financial analysis and reporting. Responsibilities: 1. Design, develop, and maintain complex Power BI reports and dashboards utilizing advanced features such as bookmarks, drill-through, and custom visuals. 2. Implement advanced data modeling techniques using Power BI Desktop, including creating calculated columns, measures, and hierarchies using DAX (Data Analysis Expressions). 3. Utilize Power Query for data transformation tasks such as merging, appending, and unpivoting data from multiple sources including MySQL databases, SQL Server, Excel files, and REST APIs. 4. Develop and optimize data models using techniques such as star schema design, role-playing dimensions, and bidirectional filtering to ensure efficient performance and scalability. 5. Implement row-level security (RLS) and dynamic security models to restrict access to sensitive data based on user roles and permissions. 6. Collaborate with database administrators and data engineers to optimize MySQL database performance and ensure seamless integration with Power BI. 7. Provide technical guidance and mentorship to junior members of the team on Power BI best practices, data modeling, and performance optimization. 8. Stay current with the latest Power BI features and updates, evaluating their potential impact on existing solutions and recommending adoption where applicable. 9. Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to Power BI reports, data refresh failures, and performance bottlenecks in collaboration with IT support teams. Requirements: 1. Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Computer Science, or related field. 2. Minimum of  3  years of experience as a Power BI Developer or similar role in the financial services industry. 3. Deep understanding of financial concepts, metrics, and reporting requirements. 4. Proficiency in Microsoft Power BI, including advanced data modeling techniques, DAX calculations, and Power Query transformations. 5. Experience working with financial databases such as SQL Server, Oracle, or MySQL. 6. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate complex financial requirements into effective Power BI solutions. 7. Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to interact effectively with finance professionals and business stakeholders. 8. Relevant certifications such as Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate or similar credentials preferred. Additional Note: Candidate may have to relocate to UAE or other Southeast Asian nation, and this position will be remote.
